Why don't you name the major long distance company?

I hate all long-distance phone companies. The whole industry is a scam. A
long time ago, I switched to Qwest long distance. But they sucked, so I
switched to another long distance company. Months after the switch, I
noticed I was receiving $15 charges from Qwest every month (it was one of
those programs where they charge you a minimum amount if you don't charge up
a high enough bill each month). I called Qwest to tell them to remove me
immediately and reimburse my charges. They said they couldn't remove me, I
needed to contact my local phone company to remove me. So I called
Ameritech, but they said I needed to contact Qwest to be removed. And the
runaround continued on while I was charged $15 each month.

The only solution is to avoid all long-distance companies period. Either use
a calling card, or use a cell phone.

I wish you the best luck in resolving your situation. You are definitely not
alone.

