"/> You need to contact the utility commissioner in the state where you're
located. Each state calls it by a different name. In California it's
called &quot;Public Utility Commission&quot;, and here in Nebraska it's called
&quot;Nebraska Public Service Commission&quot;. You can find the name of the state
regulating office in the &quot;Consumer Information&quot; section of your local phone
directory.

Several years ago I had problems with a couple of long distance carriers in
California and the Public Utility Commissioner there investigated my
problems and cleared my billing errors/disputes. It was a long and
frustrating battle, but it was finally cleared up.

These long distance carriers are absolutely ruthless. I'm sure they've only
gotten worse since I had my problems with them.

